President George W. Bush visited Iraq for the fourth and final time, defending the war he initiated in 2003.
Despite claiming progress, he faced a shoe-throwing incident during a press conference with Prime Minister Nouri al-Maliki.
The Iraqi journalist, Muntadar al-Zeidi, hurled his shoes at Bush, symbolizing the mixed feelings towards the outgoing president.
Al-Zeidi's action highlighted the resentment towards Bush's policies, reflecting the ongoing turmoil in Iraq post-Saddam Hussein's regime.
The incident underscored the complex legacy Bush leaves behind as he prepares to hand over the Iraq situation to President-elect Barack
